ZH: 我选择为伍，不愿单独行动。
EN: I choose to join the group and not go alone.

ZH: 大多数人更愿为伍，而不是独自面对困难。
EN: Most people prefer to team up rather than face difficulties alone.

ZH: 他乐于为伍，从不孤独。
EN: He enjoys being in a team and never feels lonely.

ZH: 在这个项目中，我和他为伍。
EN: I team up with him in this project.

ZH: 这个团队的成员总是为伍工作。
EN: The members of this team always work together.

ZH: 学生们喜欢和朋友为伍去上学。
EN: Students like to go to school with their friends.

ZH: 我的猫不喜欢为伍，它宁愿独自玩耍。
EN: My cat doesn't like to join in and prefers to play alone.

ZH: 在这个公司里，大家都喜欢为伍完成任务。
EN: In this company, everyone likes to team up to complete tasks.

ZH: 能够为伍的伙伴是我最好的朋友。
EN: The friends who can team up with me are my best friends.

ZH: 我忍不住为伍拍手称快。
EN: I couldn't help but applaud and cheer with the team.

ZH: 同学们互相为伍，提高学习效果。
EN: Classmates team up with each other to improve learning efficiency.

ZH: 他们为伍，挑战这个艰巨的任务。
EN: They join forces to take on this daunting task.

ZH: 这支队伍为伍，努力战胜对手。
EN: This team teams up and works hard to defeat the opponents.

ZH: 只要为伍，我们能取得更好的成绩。
EN: As long as we team up, we can achieve better results.

ZH: 在这个危险的世界里，我们为伍才能更加安全。
EN: In this dangerous world, we are only safe if we join forces.

ZH: 我们应该为伍，共同面对未来的挑战。
EN: We should team up and face future challenges together.

ZH: 为伍的经验让我们更容易攻克难题。
EN: The experience of teaming up makes it easier for us to overcome problems.

ZH: 我们为伍，克服了一个又一个困难。
EN: We team up and overcome one difficulty after another.

ZH: 只有为伍，我们才能实现梦想。
EN: Only by joining forces can we achieve our dreams.

ZH: 我们为伍，努力争取更好的未来。
EN: We team up and strive for a better future.

ZH: 为伍不仅可以提高效率，还可以增进友谊。
EN: Teaming up can not only improve efficiency but also foster friendship.
